The paper focuses on indoor localization techniques using Wi-Fi fingerprint-based approaches and incorporating built-in sensors of smartphones. This falls under the category of network and information security (cs.NI). The paper also proposes a crowdsourcing-based scheme and a trajectory clustering-based localization algorithm, which involves machine learning and data analysis, falling under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), systems and control (cs.SY), multimedia (cs.MM), and computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV).
